<TITLE>Ofélia Ramos Anunciato</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="0">Ofélia Ramos Anunciato</REFEX></REF>
 or Ofélia (1924 – 1998) was a well-known Brazilian chef. 
<REF MENTION="2" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 hosted cooking shows on TV, like A cozinha Maravilhosa de Ofélia. 
<REF MENTION="3" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">she</REFEX></REF>
 began 
<REF MENTION="4" SYNFUNC="subj-det" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="genitive" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">her</REFEX></REF>
 career as a personality chef by publishing recipes in 1958 in the newspapers A Tribuna (Santos, São Paulo) and A Gazeta (also in São Paulo). Ofélia, A Taste of Brazil is a translation from Portuguese by 
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="obj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="1"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="1">Julie Martin</REFEX></REF>
 (Melhoramentos/2000).
</PARAGRAPH>
